&lt;li&gt;Own diary management for senior stakeholders: Help those you support prioritise their time, forward-planning weeks ahead for both internal &amp;amp; external meetings, and spot &amp;amp; resolve clashes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a first point of contact: Proactively respond to requests, greet clients &amp;amp; external partners, support with ad-hoc inbox management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run meeting logistics flawlessly: Book rooms, manage catering, set-up &amp;amp; test tech, share links and pre-reads, and support with follow-up actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate travel: Flights/trains, hotels, transfers, visas (where required), detailed itineraries, and contingency planning when plans change.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support offsites and key agency events: Venue sourcing, agendas, materials, attendee coordination, dinner bookings, and follow-up actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage finance/admin processes: Raise POs, process invoices, complete timesheets, support with absence management, and handle expenses accurately and on time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support interview scheduling and onboarding: Coordinate with People team and Ogilvy TA team to confirm interviews, prep calendars/rooms, and help shape smooth induction plans for new starters.&lt;/li&gt;
